"A return convoy that will take the refugees back to Afghanistan.<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd017.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd017.jpg" onmouseover="MenuHoverEffect('li-49c3bd017', true)" onmouseout="MenuHoverEffect('li-49c3bd017', false)"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd017.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd047"><a class="hover" title="Preparing for the final leg of the journey home.<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd047.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd047.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd047.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd087"><a class="hover" title="Afghan returnee women rest at the Kabul encashment centre.<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd087.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd087.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd087.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd0c0"><a class="hover" title="At the Kandahar transit centre, families returning from Pakistan receive medical attention and immunisations before finishing the trip home to their often remote villages.<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd0c0.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd0c0.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd0c0.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd0f7"><a class="hover" title="Returnees weaving traditional carpets<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd0f7.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd0f7.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd0f7.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd127"><a class="hover" title="Afghan returnee girls are able to continue the education they received in the camps in Pakistan.<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd127.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd127.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd127.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd167"><a class="hover" title="Continuing education is often a major concern for returning refugees.<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd167.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd167.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd167.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd197"><a class="hover" title="Under its house-building programme, UNHCR provides tool kits and construction items like beams and window frames, while beneficiaries contribute most of the labour.<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd197.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd197.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd197.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd1d0"><a class="hover" title="UNHCR's housing scheme, in addition to<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd1d0.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd1d0.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd1d0.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd207"><a class="hover" title="A returnee woman bakes bread.<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd207.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd207.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd207.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd237"><a class="hover" title="The Kabul Emergency Hospital is home to many victims of war, most commonly those maimed by landmines.<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd237.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd237.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd237.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3bd267"><a class="hover" title="UNHCR's cash-for-work programme has the twin benefits of repairing a <em>karez</em> - the ancient subterranean water distribution system that feeds surrounding wells - and injecting cash into a community still struggling to become self-sufficient. Here community members gather water from a well.<br>© UNHCR/L.Slezic/Global Aware" rel="lightbox[49c3bcf77]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd267.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3bd267.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3bd267.jpg"></a></li></ul><div class="clear-both"></div><h4>Rebuilding Lives in Afghanistan</h4></div><div class="rightComponent"><div class="inlineGBlurb hidTag" id="inlineGBlurb-49c3bc205"><h2>Afghanistan: Rebuilding a War-Torn Country</h2><p>The cycle of life has started again in Afghanistan as returnees put their shoulders to the wheel to rebuild their war-torn country.</p>

<p>Return is only the first step on Afghanistan's long road to recovery. UNHCR is helping returnees settle back home with repatriation packages, shelter kits, mine-awareness training and vaccination against diseases. Slowly but surely, Afghans across the land are reuniting with loved ones, reconstructing homes, going back to school and resuming work. A new phase in their lives has begun.</p>

<p>Watch the process of return, reintegration, rehabilitation and reconstruction unfold in Afghanistan through this gallery.</p>

