0604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3cc967.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3cc967.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3cc967.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-49c3cc9b7"><a class="hover" title="The corn is served in a bowl. Qayum distributes them carefully, two cobs each. He picks out his corn, kernel by kernel, salting them liberally for flavour. His youngest daughter Aziza eats with wild abandon, oblivious to her quota. The rest eat just one and keep the rest for another meal. Lunch is washed down with tea.<br>© UNHCR/R.Arnold" rel="lightbox[49c3cc347]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3cc9b7.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49c3cc9b7.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49c3cc9b7.jpg"></a></li></ul><div class="clear-both"></div><h4>Afghans Return Home
</h4></div><div class="rightComponent"><div class="inlineGBlurb hidTag" id="inlineGBlurb-49faf8437"><h2>Zalmaï. Panoramic photo gallery
</h2><p>See Afghanistan through the eyes of a returning refugee as Afghan photographer Zalma&iuml; revisits his homeland after more than 20 years in exile. 
<p>&quot;My project tries to capture the determination and the courage of a people that has rarely known peace, their optimism against all odds, and their worry that Afghanistan could still return to the nightmarish condition it is trying to escape,&quot; says Zalma&iuml;.
<p>In addition to the emotional journey, this exhibition also marked an aesthetic milestone for the photographer. &quot;I felt that now, after such a long time, there was hope again for Afghanistan. It seemed to me that colours were returning and that they would be those of a peaceful country. And so I set out to find this hope, with &#150; for the first time &#150; colour film in my camera.&quot;
<p>Take a peep into this kaleidoscope of Zalma&iuml;'s Afghanistan. 
</div><ul class="gallery" id="inlineGallery-49faf8437" title="Zalmaï. Panoramic photo gallery
"><li class="none" id="li-49faf8440"><a class="hover" title="Internally displaced Afghans and returning refugees work together at the site of a rudimentary brick-making factory. Kandahar.<br>©  UNHCR/Zalmai/APERTURE, 2003" rel="lightbox[49faf8437]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49faf8440.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49faf8440.jpg" onmouseover="MenuHoverEffect('li-49faf8440', true)" onmouseout="MenuHoverEffect('li-49faf8440', false)"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49faf8440.jpg"></a></li><li class="none" id="li-49faf84ad"><a class="hover" title="An advertisement for a weight room and gym in Kabul. Karte Seh, Kabul.<br>©  UNHCR/Zalmai/APERTURE, 2003" rel="lightbox[49faf8437]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49faf84ad.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49faf84ad.jpg" onmouseover="MenuHoverEffect('li-49faf84ad', true)" onmouseout="MenuHoverEffect('li-49faf84ad', false)"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49faf84ad.jpg"></a></li><li class="none" id="li-49faf8525"><a class="hover" title="In many classrooms the age difference among students may be ten years or more, a legacy of the six years of education lost during the Taliban regime. Kabul.<br>©  UNHCR/Zalmai/APERTURE, 2003" rel="lightbox[49faf8437]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49faf8525.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49faf8525.jpg" onmouseover="MenuHoverEffect('li-49faf8525', true)" onmouseout="MenuHoverEffect('li-49faf8525', false)"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49faf8525.jpg"></a></li><li class="none" id="li-49faf8577"><a class="hover" title="Recently returned from exile in Iran, these young Afghans roam the streets of their village. The Taliban has destroyed their school. Faryab.<br>©  UNHCR/Zalmai/APERTURE, 2003" rel="lightbox[49faf8437]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49faf8577.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/49faf8577.jpg" onmouseover="MenuHoverEffect('li-49faf8577', true)" onmouseout="MenuHoverEffect('li-49faf8577', false)"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/49faf8577.jpg"></a></li></ul><div class="clear-both"></div><h4>Zalmaï. Panoramic photo gallery
</h4></div><div class="rightComponent"><div class="inlineGBlurb hidTag" id="inlineGBlurb-4a1155d96"><h2>Afghanistan: An Uncertain Future</h2><p>For over a quarter of a century, Afghanistan has been devastated by conflict and civil strife, with some 8 million people uprooted internally and in neighbouring countries. The overthrow of the Taliban in 2001 resulted in one of the largest and most successful return operations in history.</p>
<p>Seven years on, more than 5 million Afghan refugees have returned - increasing Afghanistan's population by an estimated 20 percent.The large majority have gone back to their areas of origin. However, some recent returnees are facing more difficulties as the country's absorption capacity reaches its limits in some areas. Last year, some Afghans returned before they were ready or able to successfully reintegrate due to the closure of refugee villages as well as the deteriorating conditions in Pakistan. In consequence, 30,000 Afghan refugees returned to further displacement in their homeland, unable to return to their villages due to conflict, lack of land, shelter materials, basic services and job opportunities. These challenges have been compounded elsewhere across the country by food insecurity and severe drought.</p>
<p>UNHCR and the Afghan Foreign Ministry highlighted the requirements for sustainable refugee return and reintegration at an international conference in Kabul in November 2008. The donor community welcomed the inclusion of refugee reintegration within the government's five-year national development strategy and the emphasis on land, shelter, water, sanitation, education, health care and livelihoods. It is anticipated that repatriation and reintegration will become more challenging in future.</p>

</div><ul class="gallery" id="inlineGallery-4a1155d96" title="Afghanistan: An Uncertain Future"><li class="none" id="li-4a11568e6"><a class="hover" title="Unable to return to her home village, an Afghan returnee from Iran struggles to make ends meet in a suburb of the western city of Herat.<br>© Zalmaï" rel="lightbox[4a1155d96]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a11568e6.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/4a11568e6.jpg" onmouseover="MenuHoverEffect('li-4a11568e6', true)" onmouseout="MenuHoverEffect('li-4a11568e6', false)"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a11568e6.jpg"></a></li><li class="none" id="li-4a1156be6"><a class="hover" title="'We came to Kabul from Pajwai in Helmand Province,' says Bismullah, a father of nine who has been displaced multiple times since returning to Afghanistan. 'We could have gone to other districts in Helmand, but there was fighting there too.'<br>© Zalmaï" rel="lightbox[4a1155d96]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a1156be6.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/4a1156be6.jpg" onmouseover="MenuHoverEffect('li-4a1156be6', true)" onmouseout="MenuHoverEffect('li-4a1156be6', false)"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a1156be6.jpg"></a></li><li class="none" id="li-4a1156df6"><a class="hover" title="A man who returned in the fall from Pakistan to a village north of Kabul readies his house for the harsh Afghan winter.<br>© Zalmaï" rel="lightbox[4a1155d96]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a1156df6.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/4a1156df6.jpg" onmouseover="MenuHoverEffect('li-4a1156df6', true)" onmouseout="MenuHoverEffect('li-4a1156df6', false)"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a1156df6.jpg"></a></li><li class="none" id="li-4a1156fb6"><a class="hover" title="Many Afghans, including returnees, flood the streets of Kabul each morning, hoping to land a job.<br>© Zalmaï" rel="lightbox[4a1155d96]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a1156fb6.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/4a1156fb6.jpg" onmouseover="MenuHoverEffect('li-4a1156fb6', true)" onmouseout="MenuHoverEffect('li-4a1156fb6', false)"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a1156fb6.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-4a1157186"><a class="hover" title="Most returnees in Kabul support themselves through sporadic day-wage labour.<br>© Zalmaï" rel="lightbox[4a1155d96]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a1157186.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/4a1157186.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a1157186.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-4a1157336"><a class="hover" title="Rehmanullah washes cars for about 30 Afghanis (60 US cents) per car. His younger siblings clean the floor mats. They also beg. Altogether, his family makes about 250-300 Afghanis per day at best.<br>© Zalmaï" rel="lightbox[4a1155d96]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a1157336.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/4a1157336.jpg"><img class="hide" alt="" src="/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a1157336.jpg"></a></li><li class="hidden" id="li-4a11574c6"><a class="hover" title="Afghan girls who grew up in exile received an education - something they would not have had access to under the Taliban in Afghanistan.<br>© Zalmaï" rel="lightbox[4a1155d96]" style="background-image: url('/web/20120604063834im_/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb0/4a11574c6.jpg');" href="/web/20120604063834/http://www.unhcr.org/thumb1/